Source: journald-archive
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Alexander <alexander.s.m@gmail.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 12)
Standards-Version: 4.5.0

Package: journald-archive
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
         systemd,
         mergerfs,
         btrfs-progs
Description: Tiered storage for systemd-journald logs
 Moves rotated journal files from /var/log/journal/ (hot, uncompressed)
 to /var/log/journal_archive/ (cold, btrfs+zstd) on a systemd timer,
 then exposes the union via mergerfs at /var/log/journal_combined/.
 .
 The hot tier stays small, so plain `journalctl` is fast on recent data.
 The cold tier benefits from btrfs zstd compression for long history.
 Use `journalctl -D /var/log/journal_combined` for full-history queries.
